2. If the first characters are not the same, return false, as they cannot be one edit distance apart.
3. If the first characters are the same, increment the pointers i and j.
4. Iterate through the strings s and t using the pointers i and j respectively.
5. If the characters at the current positions are not the same, check if they are adjacent by comparing the characters at the previous positions.
6. If the characters are not adjacent, return false.
